Stocks Erase Losses as Retailers Rise; FTSE 100 Benchmark Gains in London

-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-03-24T08:18:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/u-k-stocks-erase-their-drop-as-retailers-rise-ftse-100-index-gains-0-1-.html
U.K. stocks erased losses, led by a
rally in retailers.  The FTSE 100 Index rose 0.1 percent to 5,803.29 at 8:16
a.m. in  London  after earlier falling as much as 0.3 percent.  Kingfisher Plc, Next Plc and Marks & Spencer Group Plc all
gained more than 2 percent in london trading.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah Jones at 
 sjones35@bloomberg.net  